parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS hydraulic control unit can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to extended stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the ABS warning light is illuminated
the brake pedal hesitates to respond
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to properly diagnose and repair the brake system can lead to continued safety risks for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: Dealership refuses to replace the ABS hydraulic control unit
dealership claims the part is not available
dealership charges for diagnostic and repair services despite the recall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the vehicle fails to stop
the airbags fail to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard stays on
the airbag fails to deploy in an accident
the airbag cover is no longer flush to the dashboard
foreign objects can fall into the airbag space and cause injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled vehicles can cause drivers to continue operating their vehicles with known safety defects, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The dealership or manufacturer is unable to repair the vehicle due to parts unavailability
the repair takes an excessive amount of time
the driver is forced to continue driving a vehicle with a known safety defect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door latch and handle can cause the door to not open or close properly, leading to safety hazards, such as being trapped in the vehicle or unable to exit in an emergency situation.
symptoms: The door handle breaks or becomes inoperable
the door latch refuses to connect
the door cannot be opened or closed from the inside or outside
the door lock malfunctions
and the door handle is sharp or cuts occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door lock can cause the door to not lock or unlock properly, leading to safety and security concerns, such as being unable to secure the vehicle or being trapped inside.
symptoms: The door lock does not work
the door cannot be locked or unlocked from the inside or outside
and the door lock indicator light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dashboard and interior components can cause safety hazards, such as exposure to sharp edges or obstructed views.
symptoms: The dashboard is prematurely deteriorating
bulging
or exposing sharp edges
